OL,3,CCouple who opened private pool to the
OL,4,Cpublic face planning fight
OL,6,FMrs Gardiner added: "Schools can't
OL,7,Ffind anywhere to take the children
OL,8,Fswimming, and where the pools are open
OL,9,Fthey're fully booked so people can't
OL,10,Ffind anywhere to take their children
OL,11,Fto swim. They've found a place here,
OL,12,Fand they love it."
OL,14,FThe couple received planning consent
OL,15,Fwhen the pool was built in 2000, but
OL,16,Fdecided to look into running it as a
OL,17,Fbusiness venture when running costs
OL,18,Fescalated from #400 a month to #700 a
OL,19,Fweek last year.
